properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 10 at 10:35PM CST until January 11 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Milwaukee/Sullivan WI
properties.description:
...COMPLEX WINTER STORM WILL CONTINUE TO IMPACT THE REGION...

* WHAT...Snow tonight with some sleet and freezing drizzle. Snow
accumulation of 1 to 3 inches. Snow redevelops late Saturday
afternoon and night. An additional 3 to 7 inches expected. In
addition to the snow, strong winds gusts of 35 to 45 mph will
cause blowing and drifting of the snow Saturday night. Gusts
could reach as high as 50 mph Saturday afternoon and evening.

* WHERE...Fond du Lac, Sheboygan and Dodge Counties.

* WHEN...For the Winter Storm Warning, from noon Saturday to 6
AM CST Sunday. For the Winter Weather Advisory, from 8 PM this
evening to noon CST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. Areas of blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility. Gusty winds could
bring down tree branches.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
